Terrific display of spin bowling from Patel, taking full advantage of a low, slow, crumbling pitch

commentPostTextItems.html: A fine display from New Zealand, their first one-dayer for nine months - and all without Scott Styris and Shane Bond. Furthermore, they lost the toss - yet have beaten South Africa quite comprehensively in the end. It was, as Stephen Fleming might say in the post-match press conference, rather a good toss to lose. Graeme Smith, though he might fancy his side's ability to chase down large totals, hadn't wagered on the pitch turning quite as prodigiously as it did. Patel and Vettori - allied with sprightly, electric fielding (not to mention a brilliant spell of fast bowling from Mills) - were the difference.

We hope you enjoyed our live ball-by-ball coverage of today's match, and do keep an eye out for the bulletin, verdict and post-match quotes from the leading figures of the day. Join us tomorrow for Pakistan's match against Sri Lanka (see here for the full list of fixtures). Until then, it's goodbye.
